title: Webster Thomas cheerleaders place first at competition
text: Webster Thomas cheerleaders place first at competition Comment By Submitted to the Post Webster Post By Submitted to the Post Posted Oct. 21, 2015 at 4:00 PM Updated at 4:00 PM By Submitted to the Post Posted Oct. 21, 2015 at 4:00 PM Webster, N.Y. The Webster Thomas Cheerleaders competed Oct. 18 at the Schroeder Showdown Fall Championship. The freshman girls competed for the first time this season against Aquinas and Gates Chili and were awarded first place. The junior varsity cheerleaders also secured first place against some tough competition, including Hilton, Spencerport and Churchville Chili. Varsity competed strongly against Edison Tech, Canandaigua and Aquinas and also solidified a first-place win.
